{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5d8b5424-5ea5-4087-8316-8032c2852b34","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"097d3025-a2b8-4294-bf57-d78de56a4e94","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":303,"requestId":"7C31:26FA86:14D9BD6:176D133:69F9436F"},"id":"00769316-a7a2-4ad4-9d6d-36036d45095b","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:10:14.263Z","parentId":"75e08b8e-f594-4b75-bb67-7661984afe4b"}
